OutArcs - Class in dd.mdd.components
This class is used to represent the binding between a node and its children.
The out-going arcs (OutArcs) is represented using a simple map binding integer to node, as the MDD is determinist by default (i.e. can only have one children with a specific label).
OutArcs(int) - Constructor for class dd.mdd.components.OutArcs
Constructor.
OutArcs.Allocator - Class in dd.mdd.components
The allocator that is in charge of the OutArcs type.
When not specified, the allocator has an initial capacity of 16.
